<span id="freeTextContainer15749634520771464127">When letters from Clara Driscoll were found, they became the basis for the story &quot;Clara and Mr. Tiffany&quot;. <br/>Clara was a designer for Mr. Louis Comfort Tiffany in the late 1800&apos;s to the early 1900&apos;s. The lamps were her idea. She was inspired by nature and Mr. Tiffany.<br/>Once a woman got married she could no longer work for the company.<br/>When Clara could no longer express her creativeness and because of cut backs, she chose marriage.<br/>She was very happy with her decision.<br/>A very good book. </span>
  <span id="freeText15749634520771464127" style="display:none">When letters from Clara Driscoll were found, they became the basis for the story "Clara and Mr. Tiffany". <br />Clara was a designer for Mr. Louis Comfort Tiffany in the late 1800's to the early 1900's. The lamps were her idea. She was inspired by nature and Mr. Tiffany.<br />Once a woman got married she could no longer work for the company.<br />When Clara could no longer express her creativeness and because of cut backs, she chose marriage.<br />She was very happy with her decision.<br />A very good book. </span>
