              <span id="reviewTextContainer2555769812" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6034718290787628516">i have really just been striking out with books lately. for a while, i stuck to a rule that if i was 30% of the way into a book and i wasn&apos;t hooked, i shelved it and i think i need to get back to that. this book had its moments but for the most part, none of it really grabbed me. the very last interaction between clara and louis had me slightly choked up and the history of tiffany lamps is of more interest to me (can anyone get me a wisteria lamp under $300? lol) but i probably could have set th</span>
  <span id="freeText6034718290787628516" style="display:none">i have really just been striking out with books lately. for a while, i stuck to a rule that if i was 30% of the way into a book and i wasn't hooked, i shelved it and i think i need to get back to that. this book had its moments but for the most part, none of it really grabbed me. the very last interaction between clara and louis had me slightly choked up and the history of tiffany lamps is of more interest to me (can anyone get me a wisteria lamp under $300? lol) but i probably could have set this one aside and not felt much remorse. </span>
